Reasoning: The paper focuses on designing machine learning systems for highly distributed and rapidly growing data, which involves challenges related to communication and computation. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses ML algorithms, model structures, and training/serving data, indicating that it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also mentions non-IID data partitions, which suggests that it could belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. Furthermore, the paper discusses ML training over facial images, indicating that it could belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses low-latency and low-cost ML serving, which suggests that it could also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
